gui.analyzer.handlers

Class DomainIdentifiable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gui.analyzer.handlers.DomainIdentifiable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The component class.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractButtonHandler, CalculatorButtonHandler, CalculatorDisplayLabelHandler, CalculatorEntryLabelHandler, ContainerComposite, DialogComposite, FrameComposite, FurnitureTreeHelper, JComboBoxHandler, JFileChooserHandler, JLabelHandler, JListHandler, JMenuBarComposite, JMenuComposite, JPopupMenuSeparatorHandler, JSpinnerHandler, JTabbedPaneComposite, JTextComponentHandler, JToolBarSeparatorHandler, JTreeHandler

    public abstract class DomainIdentifiable<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Serves for extracting domain information from components. Different information can be extracted from different component types. According to the given type of component T the implementation of this class extracts the domain information from the component.
    Author:
    Michaela Bacikova

      • createTerm

        public Term createTerm(T component,
              DomainModel domainModel)
        Creates a new term with the information extracted from the provided component. The term is created using all available information which are possible to be extracted using this handler. This information includes:
        • Domain identifier - primary information, usually a name or label or JLabel text.
        • Domain descriptor - secondary information, usually a toolTip or an actionCommand name
        • Relations - a relation which is generated by this component, or a relation which is generated by this component's parent.
        • Icon - sometimes an icon can contain domain information (either text or image).
        • Constraints - for example: a data type, length, range, enumeration, regex.
        Also a reference to a the provided component and its class is stored into the Term.
        Parameters:
        component - The provided component
        domainModel - The domainModel is used only as a reference, which is stored in each term.
        Returns:
        A new Term with all information which is possible to extract from the provided component.

      • getDomainLabelDescriptor

        public javax.swing.JLabel getDomainLabelDescriptor(T component)
        In Java, a labelFor attribute is available in the JLabel components. This can be set, if the JLabel component is a label for other component. Using this attribute we can extract a domain descriptor.
        Parameters:
        component - the component for which the JLabel should be found.
        Returns:
        the textual label for the provided component extracted from a JLabel component with the labelFor attribute set to the provided component.

      • getConstraints

        public java.util.List<Constraint> getConstraints(T component)
        Returns constraints related to the Term extracted from the provided component. When overriding this method, please return the constraint list provided by superclass and add new constraints into this list.
        Parameters:
        component - The component to be used for extraction.
        Returns:
        The list of extracted constraints. If no constraints can be extracted for this type of component, then returns a new ArrayList of constraints.
